      <span lang="en">This is a basic building block, a 'primitive'.  Now there are many ways to apply this primitive, not all four sides of the hips and shoulders need be controled simultaneously.  Two points of control can be plenty.  The hip can also be controled one step lower by turking a leg, or a joint above the shoulder by rotating an elbow.</span>
